div.p:
The ſaid Truſtees did petition the Lord Keeper concerning the ſaid Infant,
                  Hilary Term laſt. complaining of the Proceedings of the ſaid Watkinſon and his Wife, and the ſaid Serjeant Gooding (pending the ſaid Bill in Chancery) and prayed that the ſaid Infant might be brought into Court, and committed to ſome indifferent Hand, untill ſhe ſhould attain her Age of Conſent;
                  12th. of February, 1696. whereupon the Lord Keeper ordered, that Watkinſon, and his Wife, and Serjeant Gooding ſhould attend him with the Infant on the next Day of Petitions.
